We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

Ensure that only expenditures that have direct bearing or falling within the concept of disaster preparedness, prevention and mitigation activities are included in the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Plan (LDRRMP) and charged to the Fund;

Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council (LDRRMC) monitor and evaluate the use and disbursement of the LDRRMF as required;

Submit a revised Annual Investment Plan (AIP) as approved by the local sanggunian and LCE upon recommendation of the LDRRMC in accordance with the approved LDRRMP for the release and utilization of the unexpended balances of LDRRMF;

Observe strictly the requirement set forth under COA Circular No. 2012-002 specifically Section 5.1.16 on the proper and adequate disclosure/discussion in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the amounts and details of the unexpended balance of LDRRMF; and

Prepare and certify the correctness of the Report on the Sources and Utilization of DRRMF and the LDRRM Officer and submit the same to the identified offices on or before the 15th day after the end of each month. Also, the LDRRM Officer should comply with the posting requirements of such reports in conspicuous places including websites, if any, of the LGU/LDRRMO.

